Put spaces around symbolic operators.

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    total = left + right
    count += 1
]

Beanstalk uses words for equality and logic:

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    same = left is right
    different = left is not right
    ready = loaded and valid
    blocked = not ready
]

Division has two forms:

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    real_result = 5 / 2
    whole_result = 5 // 2
]

`/` produces a real `Float` result. `//` performs integer division and produces
an `Int` when both values are `Int`.
